reviews.review_text: 35 year anniversary of this show This is a great AUD copy of this show. There's no continuity in the 1st set but some great songs. My favorite Peggy-O this far in my archive journey, and Black Peter is something else.  Great show, and dumb Bobby jokes. Donna sounds great, love the "disco" songs off of theTerrapin Station album. First time I've heard Dancin' live. I've only got Winterland NYE  and this one under my belt for '78 shows so far but this is a good crisp recording and worth a listen.
